# Supabase Schema

## Migration Pattern
`schema.sql` is a full destructive migration — it DROPs all tables with CASCADE then recreates.
- `DROP TABLE ... CASCADE` removes triggers and FK constraints automatically
- Do NOT use `DROP TRIGGER ... ON table` after the table is dropped — PostgreSQL errors
- Use `CREATE TABLE` (not `IF NOT EXISTS`) after dropping

## Tables (all scoped by merchant_id)
- `merchants` — one row per CloudCart store (parent table)
- `settings` — key/value pairs per merchant (composite PK: merchant_id + key)
- `tiers` — tier definitions with optional `cloudcart_group_id`
- `reward_types` — discount configurations (flat/percent/shipping × target)
- `loyalty_customers` — unique constraint on `(merchant_id, cloudcart_id)`
- `points_transactions` — audit log (type: earn/redeem/adjust/expire)
- `bonus_rules` — configurable rules with JSONB config
- `processed_orders` — idempotency (composite PK: merchant_id + cloudcart_order_id)
- `webhook_logs` — raw payloads for debugging

## Trigger
`trg_merchant_defaults` fires AFTER INSERT on `merchants` — auto-seeds default settings, tiers, and reward types for new merchants.

## Password Functions
- `hash_password(plain)` — bcrypt via pgcrypto
- `verify_merchant_password(slug, password)` — checks against stored hash
- `check_password(hash, plain)` — generic bcrypt verify
